Maso Palù

via Graziani 56, Brentonico, 38060, Italy
€€ · Regional Cuisine, Alpine
Bib Gourmand: good quality, good value cooking
An annexe to the family farm with its organic apple orchards, this rustic, welcoming restaurant situated on the road leading up towards Monte Baldo has been in business since 1984. Despite its years of experience, the management team here does not rest on its laurels but continues to serve cuisine rooted in regional traditions with just a touch of imagination and modern influence in some dishes. Open every day in summer, but only Friday to Sunday at other times of year.
